parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power
the transmission makes a grinding or whining noise
the vehicle stalls
the transmission fails to engage into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the accelerator pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle stalls
the "wrench" light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle hesitates or surges when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering can cause the vehicle to be difficult to steer, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering assist light illuminates on the dashboard
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical systems malfunction
the dashboard lights flicker or fail
the vehicle's accessories fail to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or surge forward, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or acceleration
the engine RPMs fluctuate
the "wrench" check engine light illuminates
the vehicle surges forward or stalls
the accelerator pedal becomes unresponsive
and the vehicle goes into "limp home" mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering assist fault warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the steering wheel vibrates or jerks
the vehicle pulls or tugs while driving
the vehicle loses power steering functionality.
